gomodel:SYNGO_2607  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: From Results section:\n\n\"syntaxin 1A and nSec-1/Munc18-a were efficiently co-immunoprecipitated with anti-Vps11 antibody but not by normal rabbit IgG negative controls. This interaction is specific to the syntaxin 1A and nSec-1/Munc18-a, because other core components in the neuron specific membrane fusion, such as SNAP-25 and VAMP2, did not interact (Fig. 1A). To further confirm this interaction, we performed GST-pull down assays using rat brain homogenates. The endogenous mammalian Class C Vps protein complex was efficiently retained by GST-syntaxin 1A and GST-nSec-1/Munc18-a (Fig. 1B, lane 2 and lane 5), but not GST, GST-SNAP-25, or GST-VAMP2, respectively.\"\n\n\"Synaptosomal fractions were prepared from adult rat cortex [18,19]. The distribution profile of mammalian Class C Vps proteins was almost identical to those of syntaxin 1A, nSec-1/Munc18-a, and synaptophysin, which are found in fractions containing synaptic cytosolic and vesicular proteins\"\n\n\"The Vps11-positive gold particles were observed in close proximity to the pre-synaptic plasma membrane (Fig. 3B, arrows). Using primary hippocampal neuronal cultures, mammalian Class C Vps proteins also co-localized with synapsin 1-positive processes and punctate synapses (Supplemental Fig. 2).\". Experimental description: From M&M section:\n\"For immunoprecipitation, rat brain homogenates were lysed in modified RIPA buffer.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
